{"name":"[Initiate] Start of Mystery","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>When you <strong>are in good standing with your Sect, at the beginning of each mystery</strong>, roll +Charm. On a 10+ they provide some useful info or help in the field. On a 7-9 you get a mission associated with the mystery, and if you do it you&rsquo;ll get some info or help too. On a miss, they ask you to do something bad. If you fail a mission or refuse an order, you&rsquo;ll be in trouble with the Sect until you atone.&nbsp;</p>","rating":"charm"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4a4szNe3353Dngbn"}
{"_id":"6vXwHBcexObrmjac","name":"[Initiate] Fortunes","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>The Sect has ancient prophecies or divination techniques to predict the future. Once per mystery, you may use them. If&nbsp;<strong>you look at what the future holds</strong>, roll +Weird. On a 10+ hold 3, and on a 7-9 hold 1. On a miss, you get bad information and the Keeper decides how that affects you. Spend your hold to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Have a useful object ready.</li>\n<li>Be somewhere you are needed, just in time.</li>\n<li>Take +1 forward, or give +1 forward to another hunter.</li>\n<li>Retroactively warn someone about an attack so that it doesn't happen.</li>\n</ul>","rating":"weird"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.initiate-moves.y9TiYxWE6TRydEr8"}},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"[Initiate] Mystic","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>Every time you successfully <strong>use magic</strong>, take +1 forward.</p>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6zMeHlZrdVbG5Vqx"}
{"_id":"8M0GppGqoEYRWCF6","name":"[Initiate] Helping Hand","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>When you successfully <strong>help out</strong> another hunter, they get +2 instead of the usual +1.</p>","rating":"cool"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"[Initiate] Ancient Fighting Arts","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>When using an old-fashioned hand weapon, you inflict +1 harm and get +1 whenever you roll <strong>protect someone</strong>.</p>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"K4mGTkoQQu1xfcUd"}
{"_id":"XEvzuxoguFs7YQVB","name":"[Initiate] That Old Black Magic","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>When you <strong>use magic</strong>, you can ask a question from the investigate a mystery move as your effect.</p>","rating":"weird"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mZtJlYeGb1ui4BEb","name":"[Initiate] Sacred Oath","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>You may bind yourself to a single goal, forsaking something during your quest (e.g. speech, all sustenance but bread and water, alcohol, lying, sex, etc). Get the Keeper&rsquo;s agreement on this&mdash;it should match the goal in importance and difficulty. While you keep your oath and work towards your goal, mark experience at the end of every session and get +1 on any rolls that directly help achieve the goal. If you break the oath, take -1 ongoing until you have atoned.</p>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"[Initiate] Apprentice","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>You have an apprentice: name them. Your job is to teach them the Sect&rsquo;s ways. They count as an <strong>ally: subordinate</strong> (motivation: to follow your instructions to the letter).</p>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xqioqNsuv7vFTafU"}
{"name":"[Initiate] Mentor","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>You have a mentor in the Sect: name them. When you<strong> contact your mentor for info</strong>, roll +Sharp. On a 10+, you get an answer to your question, no problem. On a 7-9 you choose: they&rsquo;re either busy and can&rsquo;t help, or they answer the question but you owe a favour. On a miss, your question causes trouble.</p>","rating":"sharp"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yd030EAFhO6sY1Wz"}
